psidev.psi.mi.jami.enricher.listener.impl

Class EntityEnricherListenerManager<P extends Entity>

  • java.lang.Object
    • psidev.psi.mi.jami.enricher.listener.impl.EnricherListenerManager<P,EntityEnricherListener<P>>
      • psidev.psi.mi.jami.enricher.listener.impl.EntityEnricherListenerManager<P>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, EnricherListener<P>, EntityEnricherListener<P>, EntityChangeListener<P>, EntityInteractorChangeListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParticipantEnricherListenerManager

    public class EntityEnricherListenerManager<P extends Entity>
extends EnricherListenerManager<P,EntityEnricherListener<P>>
implements EntityEnricherListener<P>
    A manager for listeners which holds a list of listeners. Listener manager allows enrichers to send events to multiple listeners. A listener itself, it implements all methods which will then fire the corresponding method in each entry of the listener list. No promise can be given to the order in which the listeners are fired.
    Since:
    10/07/13
    Author:
    Gabriel Aldam (galdam@ebi.ac.uk)
